-- Brazil Oil Plans Unaffected by BP's Gulf Spill, Sueddeutsche Zeitung Says
-- Rainer Buergin
-- 2010-06-15T06:41:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-15/brazil-oil-plans-unaffected-by-bp-s-gulf-spill-sueddeutsche-zeitung-says.html

          
          
             Brazil’s Deputy Foreign Minister
 Antonio de Aguiar Patriota  said the country’s plan to develop
offshore oilfields is unaffected by the spill in the Gulf of
Mexico,  Sueddeutsche Zeitung  reported.  
 “Planning continues,” Patriota said, adding that the most
advanced technologies will be used to tap Brazil’s offshore
resources. “We’re happy to welcome investors.”  
